{"schema_version":"1","crate":"bbs_embed_linux","version":"0.2.0","id":"433592909dcd7887","name":"BBS.embed.AIN.linux","qualified_name":"BBS.embed.AIN.linux","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"bbs-embed-ain-linux.ads","line":33,"column":9},"code":"package BBS.embed.AIN.linux","documentation":{"description":"\nThe analog related pins for the BeagleBone Black are:\nAIN0 - P9_39\nAIN1 - P9_40\nAIN2 - P9_37\nAIN3 - P9_38\nAIN4 - P9_33\nAIN5 - P9_36\nAIN6 - P9_35\nVdd_ADC - P9_32\nGnd_ADC - P9_34\n\nThe processor datasheet indicates that there are actually 8 analog inputs, but\nperhaps one of them may not be brought out to a processor pin.  The analog inputs\nappear to be part of a touch screen system, but accessing those functions may\nrequire writing a specific linux device driver.\n\nThere are no pin control files for these pins - they are dedicated to analog\ninput."},"tagged_types":[{"id":"16ee6055ab8ba79b","name":"Linux_AIN_record","qualified_name":"BBS.embed.AIN.linux.Linux_AIN_record","kind":"ada_tagged_type","location":{"file":"bbs-embed-ain-linux.ads","line":54,"column":9},"code":"type Linux_AIN_record is new AIN_record with private;","documentation":{"description":"\nCreate a new AIN object"},"parent_type":{"qualified_name":"BBS.embed.AIN.AIN_record","id":"4fda88701d4e00b2","unit":"bbs-embed-ain-ain_record"},"dispatching_declared":[{"qualified_name":"BBS.embed.AIN.linux.close","id":"45288c1bc3fa71dd","unit":"bbs-embed-ain-linux"},{"qualified_name":"BBS.embed.AIN.linux.configure","id":"5e8836fc81ecefb8","unit":"bbs-embed-ain-linux"},{"qualified_name":"BBS.embed.AIN.linux.get","id":"cd09e64b7a8c92df","unit":"bbs-embed-ain-linux"}],"dispatching_overridden":[{"qualified_name":"BBS.embed.AIN.linux.get","id":"5584e8738ba20a53","unit":"bbs-embed-ain-linux"}],"prefix_callable_declared":[{"qualified_name":"BBS.embed.AIN.linux.close","id":"45288c1bc3fa71dd","unit":"bbs-embed-ain-linux"},{"qualified_name":"BBS.embed.AIN.linux.configure","id":"5e8836fc81ecefb8","uni